Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
exportPowerSwitch(25.10)                              exportPowerSwitch(25.10)

Name
       exportPowerSwitch - Exports power switch database

Syntax
       exportPowerSwitch

       [-help]

       [-powerDomain <powerDomainName>]

       [-file <fileName>]

       Exports power switch database. The command is needed in cases of defIn-
       based  flows  where power switch database required for power switch re-
       lated operations is not loaded through defIn. So, use exportPowerSwitch
       to save power switch database after power switch  insertion  using  ad-
       dPowerSwitch for later use, which can be loaded back using importPower-
       Switch.

       For  example,  in  case  power  switches are inserted at the Floor Plan
       stage and the power switch database is exported for further use in  the
       flow,  the  following command executed after floorplan for power Domain
       PD1, will save the power switch information into the PD1_powerswitch.db
       file:

       exportPowerSwitch -powerDomain PD1 -file PD1_powerswitch.db

       Post running the above command, if the floorplan DEF  is  used  in  the
       flow  from  synthesis,  the stored power switch information needs to be
       restored using the importPowerSwitch command from the  database,  which
       was  earlier stored using the exportPowerSwitch command after floorplan
       and before placement.

       Note: The enable net IN and OUT connections should remain the  same  in
       the netlist in power switch database export/import process and the com-
       mands  need  not  be  run when saveDesignand defOut are run because the
       power switch database is automatically saved and restored.

PSO File Generation and Usage
       A PSO file gets generated as an output of  the  exportPowerSwitch  com-
       mand,  which  can  be used in a future session, if needed. One scenario
       where this file can be needed is when a DEF  file  containing  a  power
       switch  chain  is  not used in the power switch synthesis and hence the
       incoming netlist to Innovus would not  have  any  power  switches.  The
       power  switch  chain is then created at the init stage of Innovus using
       the addPowerSwitch command in  such  a  run.  A  database  saved  using
       write_db  after running the addPowerSwitch command, will have the power
       switch chain saved in a <design.pso> file. When restored, this database
       can also be used to write out the saved PSO file using the exportPower-
       Switch command. When the power switches are added using  the  addPower-
       Switch  command,  the reportPowerSwitch command can be used to validate
       their addition.

       To avoid regenerating power switches  in  future  implementation  runs,
       save  the  power switch chain using the exportPowerSwitch command along
       with the floorplan DEF. Ensure that the -routing parameter of  the  de-
       fOut command is also used along with -floorplan and -noStdCells to save
       the power switch network under the NETS section of the DEF.

       Refer to the following flows to understand the usage of the PSO file:

       Innovus Session 1:

       <init Design1 - incoming design has no power switches>

       addPowerSwitch

       exportPowerSwitch test.pso

       defOut -floorplan -noStdCells -routing test.def

       Innovus Session 2:

       <init Design2 - incoming design has no power switches>

       importPowerSwitch -file test.pso

       defIn test.def

       While  reading  the DEF file, you can identify the power switches using
       the database commands, such as  get_db  and  dbIsCellPowerSwitch,  even
       without using the importPowerSwitch command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each exportPowerSwitch parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man exportPowerSwitch.

       -powerDomain <powerDomainName>
              Specifies  the power domain whose power switch information is to
              be exported.

       -file <fileName>
              Specifies the name of the export file.

